entry.title: The Pension Protection Fund (Multi-employer Schemes) (Modification) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations are made under section 307(1)(b) and (2)(b) and (e) of the Pensions Act 2004 (c. 35) (“the Act”) which contain a power to modify the provisions of Part 2 and section 286 of the Act as they apply in relation to multi-employer schemes. Part 2 of the Act makes provision in respect of the functions of the Board of the Pension Protection Fund (“the Board”) which is established under section 107 of the Act. Section 286 of the Act makes provision in respect of the financial assistance scheme for members of certain pension schemes.

entry.title: The Patents (Translations) Rules 2005
entry.summary: These Rules implement Article 1(1) of the Agreement on the application of Article 65 of the Convention on the Grant of European Patents made in London on 17th October 2000 (“the London Agreement”). The London Agreement is published as Cm 5247 Miscellaneous Series No. 9 (2001).

entry.title: The National Health Service (General Ophthalmic Services) (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the National Health Service (General Ophthalmic Services) (Scotland) Regulations 1986 (“the principal Regulations”), which provide for arrangements under which ophthalmic medical practitioners and ophthalmic opticians provide general ophthalmic services under the National Health Service.

entry.title: The Insolvency Practitioners and Insolvency Services Account (Fees) (Amendment) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order makes amendments to the Insolvency Practitioners and Insolvency Services Account (Fees) Order 2003 (S.I. 2003/3363). Article 2 amends the Schedule to the 2003 Order to make provision for the circumstances where an account relating to monies held in the Insolvency Services Account will no longer be regarded as being “maintained”. Where an account ceases to be maintained this terminates liability for the payment of fees under the 2003 Order.

entry.title: The Community Care (Direct Payments) (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations are made under sections 12B(1)(b) and 90(3) of the Social Work (Scotland) Act 1968 (“the 1968 Act”). Section 12B was originally inserted into the 1968 Act by section 4 of the Community Care (Direct Payments) Act 1996. Section 12B was amended by section 70 of the Regulation of Care (Scotland) Act 2001 and section 7 of, and paragraph 1 of Schedule 2 to, the Community Care and Health (Scotland) Act 2002.

entry.title: The Advice and Assistance (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Advice and Assistance (Scotland) Regulations 1996 to provide that a solicitor’s right to prior payment of fees and outlays out of any property recovered or preserved for a client in respect of advice and assistance shall not apply to the first £4,531 recovered or preserved by virtue of certain family proceedings (this sum is increased from £4,395).

entry.title: The A21 Trunk Road (School Hill and Spray Hill, Lamberhurst) (Restricted Road) Order 2005
entry.summary: This version of the The A21 Trunk Road (School Hill and Spray Hill, Lamberhurst) (Restricted Road) Order 2005 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The Road Traffic (Health Services Charges) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Road Traffic (Health Services Charges) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2001 (“the principal Regulations”) which provide for a scheme for the recovery from insurers and certain other persons of charges in connection with the health services treatment of road traffic casualties.

entry.title: The Civil Proceedings Fees (Amendment) Order 2005

ukm:Subject.Value: SUPREME COURT OF ENGLAND AND WALES

category.term: SUPREME COURT OF ENGLAND AND WALES

entry.summary: Under article 4(2)(b) of the Civil Proceedings Fees Order 2004 (S.I. 2004/3121) there is a maximum gross annual income taken into account for the purposes of working tax credit, above which working tax credit will not be a qualifying benefit for the purposes of exemption from court fees under the Order. This Order amends that maximum gross annual income, from £14,600 to £15,050.

entry.title: The Family Proceedings Fees (Amendment) Order 2005

ukm:Subject.Value: SUPREME COURT OF ENGLAND AND WALES

category.term: SUPREME COURT OF ENGLAND AND WALES

entry.summary: Under article 3(2)(b) of the Family Proceedings Fees Order 2004 (S.I. 2004/3114) there is a maximum gross annual income taken into account for the purposes of working tax credit, above which working tax credit will not be a qualifying benefit for the purposes of exemption from court fees under the Order. This Order amends that maximum gross annual income, from £14,600 to £15,050.

entry.title: The Trade in Controlled Goods (Embargoed Destinations) (Amendment) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order amends the Trade in Controlled Goods (Embargoed Destinations) Order 2004 (“the 2004 Order”).

entry.title: The Trade in Goods (Control) (Amendment) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order amends the Trade in Goods (Control) Order 2003 (“the 2003 Order”).

entry.title: The A21 Trunk Road (Lamberhurst) (Derestriction) Order 2005
entry.summary: This version of the The A21 Trunk Road (Lamberhurst) (Derestriction) Order 2005 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The Insolvency (Amendment) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Insolvency Regulations 1994 (S.I. 1994/2507). Regulation 6 of these Regulations inserts a new regulation 3A into the Insolvency Regulations 1994 to make provision for when the Secretary of State can require information from an administrator and the circumstances in which an administrator can dispose of company’s records.

entry.title: The Civil Legal Aid (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2005
entry.summary: This version of the The Civil Legal Aid (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2005 is the published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer for Scotland. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The Sunderland Teaching Primary Care Trust (Transfer of Trust Property) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order transfers to the South of Tyne and Wearside Mental Health National Health Service Trust, trust property held by the Sunderland Teaching Primary Care Trust and makes related provision. A copy of the schedule of trust property transferred under this Order can be obtained from the Department of Health, Quarry House, Quarry Hill, Leeds LS2 7UE.

entry.title: The Information Tribunal (Enforcement Appeals) (Amendment) Rules 2005
entry.summary: These Rules, which have been prepared in consultation with the Council on Tribunals, make a small number of amendments to the Information Tribunal (Enforcement Appeals) Rules 2005 (S.I. 2005/14).

entry.title: The Agricultural Subsidies (Appeals) (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Agricultural Subsidies (Appeals) (Scotland) Regulations 2004 (“the principal Regulations”) to add to the list of decisions amenable to review and appeal set out in regulation 4 of the principal Regulations certain decisions made under Council Regulation (EC) No. 1782/2003 (O.J. No. L 270, 21.10.2003, p.1; “the Council Regulation”), Commission Regulation (EC) No. 2237/2003 (O.J. No. L 339, 24.12.2003, p.52; “Commission Regulation 2237/2003”), Commission Regulation (EC) No. 795/2004 (O.J. No. L 141, 30.4.2004, p.1; “Commission Regulation 795/2004”), Commission Regulation (EC) No. 796/2004 (O.J. No. L 141, 30.4.2004, p.18) (“the CAP reform Community instruments”) and other legislation implementing those Regulations. They come into force on 18th March 2005.

entry.title: The Export of Goods, Transfer of Technology and Provision of Technical Assistance (Control) (Amendment) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order amends the Export of Goods, Transfer of Technology and Provision of Technical Assistance (Control) Order 2003 (“the 2003 Order”).

entry.title: The A21 Trunk Road (Lamberhurst Bypass) (24 Hours Clearway) Order 2005
entry.summary: This version of the The A21 Trunk Road (Lamberhurst Bypass) (24 Hours Clearway) Order 2005 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.
